{
  "text": "Glaucoma includes various types of open-angle, closed-angle and normal-tension glaucoma, and results in damage to the optic nerve and vision loss [CITATION_1] . The risk factors of glaucoma include increased pressure in the eye and family history of high blood pressure, obesity and migraines [CITATION_2] . Once vision loss from glaucoma occurs, it will be permanent [CITATION_3] . Therefore, the exact pathogenesis requires research for prevention, diagnosis and treatment of glaucoma.",
